						               													<description>From the publisher:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;quot;There is no knowing what he can do, or may choose to try. A wild beast cornered is not safe to approach. And Saruman has powers you do not guess. Beware of his voice!&amp;quot;&amp;#10;     &amp;ndash;Gandalf, The Two Towers&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Combined in one single, sixty-card package, The Treason of Saruman Nightmare Decks for The Lord of the Rings: The Card Game introduce new setup and encounter decks that greatly increase the difficulty of the three scenarios from The Treason of Saruman Saga Expansion.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;With a focus on the treacherous Wizard and his fearsome Uruk-hai, these Nightmare Decks raise the stakes of your adventures with Aragorn and company as you pursue your captive companions, fight alongside the Rohirrim at the defense of Helm's Deep, and march against the fortress of Isengard. Simultaneously, they introduce new themes and story elements, such as the arrival of Mauhur&amp;rsquo;s Orcs and the dastardly effect of Saruman&amp;rsquo;s Wizardry.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
